quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  14,34,"And He hath vouchsafed unto you some of everything ye asked Him. And if ye would count Allah's favours, ye can not compute them; verily man is a great wrong-doer, highly ungrateful"
  14,35,"And recall what time Ibrahim said: my Lord! make this City secure and keep me and my sons away from worshipping the idols"
  14,36,"My Lord! they have sent astray many among mankind; whosoever followeth me, verily he is of me; and whosoever disobeyeth me, then verily Thou art Forgiving, Merciful"
  14,37,"Our Lord! verily have caused some of my progeny to dwell in a valley uncultivable near Thy Sacred House, Our Lord! in order that they may establish prayer; make Thou therefore the hearts of some of mankind to Yearn toward them, and provide them Thou With fruits, haply they may give thanks"
  14,38,Our Lord! verily Thou knowest that which We conceal and that which We make known; and not of aught is concealed from Allah in the earth or in the heaven
  14,39,"All praise be unto Allah who hath bestowed upon me, despite old age lsma'il and ls-haq; verily my Lord is the Hearer of supplication"
  14,40,"My Lord! make me establisher of prayer and also from my progeny, our Lord! and accept Thou my supplication"
  14,41,Our Lord! forgive me and my parents and the believers on the Day whereon will be set up the reckoning
  14,42,"And deem not Allah negligent of that which the wrong-doers work: He only deferreth them to a Day whereon the sighthall remain staring"